fields.public_access_description: This is a rare toy kitchen complete with its collection of utensils, tools, oven and hen coop. This was a popular and attractive present to give a girl to introduce her to the domestic skills that she was going to need to run her own household later on.. Kitchens were also portable and much easier to carry than dolls' houses as well as being easier to export. Room settings in general almost superseded the dolls' house in Germany in popularity by the beginning of the 19th century. Contemporary and reproduction kitchens are still being made today.
